    About San Antonio Shoemakers™ 
</asp:Content>
<asp:Content ID="Content3" ContentPlaceHolderID="ContentPlaceHolder2" Runat="Server">
    <p class="auto-style4">
    San Antonio Shoemakers™ started in 1976 by two friends, Terry Armstrong and Lew Hayden.
</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    Headquartered in San Antonio, Texas.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    How to say our name: Although our full name is San Antonio Shoemakers™, sometimes we are referred to by our abbreviated name, which is SAS, or (‘es\’a\‘es).
</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    A majority of SAS products are handcrafted in San Antonio and Del Rio, Texas.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    SAS has two factories in Texas: San Antonio (est. 1976) and Del Rio (est. 1985).</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    SAS recently partnered with a family-owned Italian company to design and manufacture a quality dress shoe in conjunction with SAS master shoemakers.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    SAS Shoe Factory and General Store located on the south side of San Antonio.
</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    Sold in stores throughout the US, also sold internationally.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    Our focus: quality and craftsmanship.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    SAS uses the finest leather and quality materials.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    SAS shoes are designed with an innovative comfort system for all-day wear.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    Wide variety of sizes and widths: 88 for women, 104 for men.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    More styles and colors to offer than in the past including leather handbag collection.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    New stores are updated with a boutique setting for an upscale shopping experience.</p>
<p class="auto-style4">
    You can stop in to be personally fitted by a professional shoe-fitter to find the right size and style for you in any SAS store.</p>
